The paper discusses the challenges and inconsistencies in communicating uncertainty in visualizations, which is a common issue in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and graphics (cs.GR) research. The paper also mentions the use of data-driven reports (cs.CV) and consumer applications, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI) categories.
